==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[sorh]], from Germanic ''*surgō''.  Cognate with Dutch [[zorg]], German [[Sorge]], Swedish [[sorg#Swedish|sorg]].

===Pronunciation===
*sŏr'ō, /ˈsɒrəʊ/, /"sQrəU/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒrəʊ|-ɒrəʊ]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sorrow|sorrows}}
#(''uncountable'') [[unhappiness]], [[woe]]
#(''countable, usually in plural'') An instance or cause of unhappiness.

